  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Utilising landscape scale forest ecosystem rehabilitation as a cost effective bridge for the integrated deployment of national land-based mitigation and adaptation strategies</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The rehabilitation of forest ecosystems &#x2013; in an ecologically and socially compatible way and at a larger landcape scale &#x2013; can provide a bridge while maximizing co-benefits for communities and biodiversity. This project piloted initiatives to optimize the implementation of actions that simultaneously contribute to both land-based mitigation and adaptation strategies via landscape scale forest ecosystem rehabilitation. It achieved this goal by: (1) Identifying national &#x201C;best bets&#x201D; for optimizing coherent implementation of land-based mitigation and adaptation strategies; (2) Supporting national policy and programme development that integrates the &#x201C;best bets&#x201D;; and (3) Stimulating commitment among decision-makers and investors through global analysis, networking and policy influence.</narrative>
  </description>
